FACILITIES AGREEMENT THIS AMENDED AND RESTATED CO-TENANCY AND SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT (this "Agreement") is made and entered into as of September 8, 2015 (the "Agreement Date") by and among GRANT WIND, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company ("Grant"), GRANT PLAINS WIND, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company ("Grant Plains", and collectively with Grant, the "Co-Tenants"), GRANT COUNTY INTERCONNECT, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company agreement ("GCI"), and Grant, as Shared Facilities Manager (the "Shared Facilities Manager") (the Shared Facilities Manager, GCI and the Co-Tenants are sometimes hereinafter referred to individually as a "Party" and collectively as the "Parties"). RECITALS: A. Grant owns assets in Grant County, Oklahoma that are sufficient to develop a wind power project (the "Grant Project") having a generating capacity of approximately 151.8 MW. B. Grant Plains owns assets in the vicinity of the Grant Project that are sufficient to develop a wind power project (the "Grant Plains Project") having a generating capacity of up to 148.2 MW. C. The Grant Project and the Grant Plains Project are sometimes referred to herein individually as a "Project", and collectively as the "Projects" (as further hereinafter defined). D. Grant is causing to be constructed on the land described in Exhibit A (such land, as may be adjusted from time to time in accordance with Section 7.9 of the Asset Purchase Agreement, the "Shared Premises")) the generator tie-line and other equipment and facilities described on Exhibit B, for the contemplated common use by the Co-Tenants for the interconnection of the Projects to the transmission system owned and operated by the Transmitting Utility (collectively, the "Shared GenLead Assets"). E. Grant holds the easement interests described on Exhibit C with respect to the Shared Premises, which easement interests permit or allow use of the Shared GenLead Assets (such easement interests, together with any related obligations or restrictions, the "Shared GenLead Real Property Rights", and together with the Shared GenLead Assets and any additional assets so designated under this Agreement, the "Shared Facilities"). F. Grant Plains (or one or more of its Affiliates) may in the future develop the Grant Plains Project, and Grant has, on the terms and subject to the conditions of the Asset Purchase Agreement, granted to Grant Plains an Option to acquire an Undivided Interest in and to the Shared Facilities. G. GCI is wholly-owned by the Co-Tenants and was formed for the sole purpose of being a party to and administering the GIA on behalf of its members, in coordination with this Agreement and the Coordination Agreements. {00032388.DOCX v6} -2- ny-1201747 H. To govern their respective rights and obligations with respect to the Shared Facilities and the expenses attributable thereto, the Parties are entering into this Agreement, which will be the Parties' expression of their intention to establish and impose mutually beneficial limitations, restrictions, covenants and conditions to provide for the proper and orderly ownership, operation and management of their interests in the Shared Facilities. I. The Co-Tenants wish to retain the Shared Facilities Manager to provide day-to-day, routine operation and maintenance service for the Shared Facilities, which service the Shared Facilities Manager will cause the Provider to provide on the terms and subject to the conditions of the Shared Facilities Services Agreement. J. Grant, Grant Plains and Apex Wind Asset Management, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company ("AWAM"), as Shared Facilities Manager, entered into that Co-Tenancy and Shared Facilities Agreement dated as of June 29, 2015 (the "Original Agreement") in respect of the Shared Facilities. Grant and Grant Plains now wish to amend and restate the Original Agreement, including to remove AWAM from its capacity as Shared Facilities Manager. Modify or alter the Shared Facilities or any component thereof in a manner that materially alters the function, output or efficiency of the Shared Facilities or any component thereof except as provided in the Annual Shared Facilities Operating Plan or agreed to in writing by all of the members of the Owners Committee. C. Execution of Documents. GRANT WIND, LLC
MARKET-BASED RATE TARIFF
1. Availability: Seller makes electric energy and capacity available under this Tariff to any purchaser for resale, except as prohibited below. Seller also makes available to any purchaser the ancillary services listed in this Paragraph 1:
MISO: Seller offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. (MISO) and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to MISO.
Southwest Power Pool: Seller offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Southwest Power Pool, Inc. (SPP) and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to SPP.
Third Party Ancillary Services: Seller offers Regulation and Frequency Response Service, Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service, Energy and Generator Imbalance Service, Operating Reserve-Spinning, and Operating Reserve-Supplemental. Sales will not include the following: (1) sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e., where that entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; and (2) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier. Sales of Operating Reserve-Spinning and Operating Reserve-Supplemental will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except where the Commission has granted authorization. Sales of Regulation and Frequency Response Service and Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except at rates not to exceed the buying public utility transmission provider's OATT rate for the same service or where the Commission has granted authorization.
2. Applicability: This Tariff is applicable to all wholesale sales of electric energy, capacity, and ancillary services by Seller, which are (a) subject to the jurisdiction of the Commission, and (b) not made pursuant to another tariff on file with the Commission.
3. Rates: All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Seller.
4. Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and Seller.
5. Seller Category: Seller is a Category 2 Seller, as defined in 18 CFR ? 35.36(a), in the Southwest Power Pool region and a Category 1 Seller, as defined in 18 C.F.R. ? 35.36(a), in the Northwest, Central, Northeast, Southeast, and Southwest regions.
6. Compliance with Commission Regulations: Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Seller to engage in affiliate sales under this Tariff or otherwise restricts or limits Seller's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this Tariff.
7. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: Seller has received waiver of: Subparts B and C of Part 35, except for sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 35.16; Part 41, Part 101 (with the exception that waiver of the provisions of Part 101 that apply to hydropower licensees has not been granted with respect to licensed hydropower projects), and Part 141, except sections 141.14 and 141.15; and received blanket approval as to Section 204 of the FPA and Part 34 of the Commission's regulations for all future issuances of securities and debt and assumptions of liabilities. Grant Wind, LLC, Unpublished Letter Order dated June 12, 2015, Docket No. ER15-2191-000. Seller is subject to restrictions on sales of energy set forth in Southern Company Services, Inc., FERC Electric Tariff Second Revised Volume No. 4, that prohibit certain market-based energy sales for delivery at a point in the Southern Balancing Authority Area during auction bid periods specified under the Southern Company Energy Auction, as accepted in Southern Company Services, Inc., 125 FERC ? 61,317 (2008). See Southern Company Services, Inc., 129 FERC ? 61,222, P 8 (2009).
8. Effective Date: This Tariff shall be effective on the date set by the Commission. 1
